Junior Software Developer (Project Based) 
Project: Part Time Position (est. 6 months) 
Position Summary   
Are you interested in gaining experience in two of the fastest growing career fields? Do you enjoy complex problem solving within a team environment? Softheon is offering current college students an opportunity to work in the exciting fields of software development, healthcare, and fintech informatics. Conveniently located on Stony Brook Universitys campus and with flexible work schedules, students can balance the demands of their education while gaining valuable experience.  
As a Part Time Junior Software Developer on the Softheon DGS (Document Generation Service) migration project, you will be responsible for migrating Softheons legacy document generation system into a new Softheon product called Softheon DGS.  Softheon DGS will transform the way we currently generate documents and consumer correspondence to a more scalable solution.  This project is expected to last 3  6 months and upon completion may be eligible to turn into a full-time position within Softheon.    
Requirements 
Critical Responsibilities  

Review and understand DGS requirements and use case documentation;   

Create data structures as basis for legacy migration;   

Following guidelines, design and implement user-friendly HTML based templates;   

Convert mockup documents into HTML;   

Ensure HTML templates meet accessibility requirements, such as WCAG compliance, on the equity portal;   

Create test cases in Softheons automated testing framework;   

Perform user acceptance testing;   

Enhance DGS use case documentation;  

Ensures project follows timeline provided by Senior Management    
Position Requirements    

Currently pursing B.S./M.S. in Computer Science or related degree;   

Minimum of 16 hours/week;   

Strong HTML/CSS skills;   

Strong communication and interpersonal skills;   

Familiar and comfortable with working in an Agile development environment;   

Experience with basic web development;   

Knowledge of JavaScript is a plus    
When you join Softheon, you will:   

Have an opportunity to be part of a great team of professionals;   

Learn and work in an environment surrounded by our Softheonites right here at the Center of Excellence in Wireless Info & Technology (CEWIT) building at Stony Brook University, NY. CEWIT is an unparalleled resource, advancing the science and technology underlying the next epoch of the information revolution (www.cewit.org)   

Receive competitive salary and career growth opportunities that includes health care, dental, vision, life insurance, flexible spending, 401k and tuition reimbursement benefits package.    
ABOUT US:  
At Softheon we strive to create simple solutions to complex problems. Our innovative and easy-to-use products have revolutionized the way everyday people control their healthcare needs. Empowering the nation's first state health benefit exchange since 2008, Softheon's vision and strategic direction has designed five platforms to help our partners quickly adapt to industry standards, manage client data, and grow their membership, while never compromising the exceptional care they provide. In this highly dynamic industry, Softheon has maintained its position as a premier Business Process as a Service (BPaaS) and Software as a Service (SaaS) solution, utilized by 37% of healthcare payers and having been responsible for 12% of ACA enrollments processed. Our platform has been ranked #1 in addressing the industrys ever-changing regulatory demands and recognized by Gartner, IDC, AHIP, ACAP, and HCEG.  
To find out more about Softheon please visitwww.softheon.com.  
To all recruitment agencies: Softheon does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to Softheon employees or any other company location. Softheon is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes and will not pay fees to any third-party agency or company that does not have a signed agreement with the Company. 

